If I’m being completely honest with you, this year was not my best. There had been many health scares, many arguments, a lot of self doubt, so much crying, and repeated mistakes with very few growth. But life isn’t perfect, some years are better than others. We have to go through it to grow from it. I decided to go back to therapy this year. I did learn a lot and I have so much more of an understanding of what I want out of life. One good thing came this year, my new home. My safe place where I spent most of the second half of this year at, I moved in, in July. My wife and I have put so much thought and energy into each piece of decor in our home. I feel happy here. I feel safe. And I feel accomplished. Which is something I haven’t felt in a long time. Let’s cheers to a happier and stronger year in 2024. Remember, it’s an achievement on its own just getting through it, and I sure did. Happy new years everyone! #furniture #home #decor #lifestyle #cozyhome
